column1: @stanwegner That's real video from the DRACO camera aboard the #DARTMission.
You can watch and listen to the full briefing on demand on the @NASAJPL YouTube channel: https://t.co/7AlkLqFm6k
@Snoopy @nasahqphoto @NASAArtemis @NASA_Orion See today's full gallery #AstronautSnoopy images from @nasahqphoto here: https://t.co/W5ADUieHvI https://t.co/5u07EJdnWN
Singer @JoshGroban and jazz pianist @HerbieHancock performed “The Star-Spangled Banner” in honor of the historic launch of the #Artemis I mission around the Moon. https://t.co/nhS7pB5mI8

How does NASA celebrate the holidays? @NASA_Astronauts and our space storytellers share the details in a special episode of our Curious Universe podcast: https://t.co/l6n9pIU62A https://t.co/h0bFXIeZrQ

LIVE NOW: Following the successful splashdown of the #Artemis I mission to the Moon and back our experts are on @Reddit and ready to take your questions! Ask us anything! https://t.co/zXGRs9QI84 https://t.co/7FumEUYfTi

NASA scientists are at #AGU22 this week discussing topics ranging from sea level change to exploring oceans on other worlds to the #Artemis I mission. Follow @NASAExhibit for updates and discover when to tune in: https://t.co/vdamkEHlSM https://t.co/yVmbQbuSeU

Some of the brightest objects in space are blazars—supermassive black holes feeding off material which can create two powerful jets of high-speed particles. A recent discovery using IXPE data solves a mystery 40 years in the works: https://t.co/ohy0vsiJfN #BlackHoleFriday https://t.co/D5VW6ae0ej

Talk about showing both sides of the story. Nice frontback Orion. On flight day 9 @NASA_Orion took these images looking forward to the Moon and back home toward Earth. More full-res images: https://t.co/pUudalErEr Track #Artemis I in real time: https://t.co/fCVt3jyqwy https://t.co/bnY0uXbWnh

We're working with @ESA to plan one of the most ambitious feats ever attempted in space—bringing a Mars sample to Earth. The Mars Sample Return campaign could help answer a question rovers alone cannot: Was there life on Mars? Here's how we plan to do it: https://t.co/vEqW0DJUlq https://t.co/Owoz2aHrKv
